stanford jazz mentors events at stanford stanford jazz mentors facebook twitter email print add to calendar the jazz mentors are selected from nearly 200 applicants from all over the country to teach at the workshop's summer education programs they gain teaching experience under the supervision of sjw's master jazz teachers they get an opportunity to play with the rest of the faculty and they spend a lot of time jamming together alumni of the program have gone on to begin outstanding careers in jazz performance and education this year's mentors have a classic horn powered front line supported by a heck of a swinging rhythm section they play their own compositions and arrangements with sensitivity power and excitement when thursday july 21 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where campbell recital hall 541 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $24 general $14 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27971 more info last modified july 15 2011
